8,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705207,"age":100,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":102,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"John Wichingham was born in 1485, in Euston, Suffolk, England. He married Mrs John Wickingham about 1512, in Euston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in Somme, Picardie, France."},"et":{"1485–":"1485–Surnud","1495–Female":"1495–Surnud","1512–1544":"1512–1544","1514–1563":"1514–1563","1485–Male":"1485–Surnud","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1512":"1512","1544":"1544","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1563":"1563","1485":"1485","1495":"1495","ABT 1512":"umbes 1512","1549":"1549","Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, England","Y, Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Of, Fishley and Euston, Suffolk, England":"Euston, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–":"1485–Kuollut","1495–Female":"1495–Kuollut","1512–1544":"1512–1544","1514–1563":"1514–1563","1485–Male":"